netsh interface portproxy add v4tov4 listenport=80 connectport=8000 connectaddress=1.1.2.3.4

# What it does

This sets up a port forwarding (proxy) rule on Windows:

Listens on port 80 (HTTP) on your local machine
Forwards any incoming traffic to:
IP: 192.1.2.3.4
Port: 8000
In plain English

“Anything hitting my computer on port 80 → send it to 192.1.2.3.4:8000.”
